"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-voices-paris-olympics-team-gb-john-major-national-lottery-b2589516.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  During his time in charge of the country, John Major cut a faintly ridiculous figure and was at the mercy of his deeply divided party.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 258, \"end\": 268, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.620758555161597e-40, \"text\": \"John Major\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, nearly 30 years later, his contribution to British sport is worth its weight in gold, saysSimon Walters  Removed from bookmarks  John Major did not get much creditwhen he was Conservative prime minister.\", \"from\": 351, \"to\": 559, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 399, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999831544669242, \"rank\": 1.6509368889172464e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He never escaped the shadow of his famous predecessor,Margaret Thatcher.\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 633, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 615, \"end\": 632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margaret_Thatcher\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 1.103096124501415e-12, \"text\": \"Margaret Thatcher\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margaret_Thatcher\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Margaret_Thatcher\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was cruelly mocked for allegedly tucking his shirtinside his underpants- and he led his party to alandslide election defeat in 1997.\", \"from\": 634, \"to\": 769, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But nearly 30 years later, one of his less well-known decisions is being creditedfor the stunning success of British athletes in Paris.\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 906, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 880, \"end\": 887, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999831544669242, \"rank\": 1.6509368889172464e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 900, \"end\": 905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999987621777, \"rank\": 1.2376668214621478e-09, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Many of the medalists have sung the praisesof the National Lottery, saying they would never have achieved Olympic glory but for the financial backing they have received from it.\", \"from\": 908, \"to\": 1085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 958, \"end\": 974, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9790195328852137, \"rank\": 0.021430080186667894, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They have unsung John Major to thank for that.\", \"from\": 1087, \"to\": 1133, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1104, \"end\": 1114, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.620758555161597e-40, \"text\": \"John Major\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The before and after effects of Major's lottery and its backing for athletics is remarkable.\", \"from\": 1135, \"to\": 1227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In 1996, the year before he left office, Britain's Olympic reputation had sunk to an all time low.\", \"from\": 1228, \"to\": 1326, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1269, \"end\": 1276, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999957215823663, \"rank\": 3.1172543386767712e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It won just one gold medal at the Atlanta Games -Steve Redgrave in the rowing- finishing a lowly 36th in the medals table, behind Kazakhstan.\", \"from\": 1328, \"to\": 1469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1458, \"end\": 1468, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"score\": 0.9999999997558007, \"rank\": 1.704509118268243e-10, \"text\": \"Kazakhstan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kazakhstan\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At that time, British athletes received a total of \\u00a35m a year support.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1541, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1485, \"end\": 1492, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999831544669242, \"rank\": 1.6509368889172464e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Since then, they have received more than \\u00a31 billion from the lottery.\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1611, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The effect has been astonishing.\", \"from\": 1612, \"to\": 1644, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Since Atlanta, Britain has won more than 100 golds in seven Games.\", \"from\": 1646, \"to\": 1712, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1652, \"end\": 1659, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.29517187293735e-12, \"text\": \"Atlanta\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Atlanta\"}, {\"begin\": 1661, \"end\": 1668, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999957215823663, \"rank\": 3.1172543386767712e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It came fourth in the medals table in Beijing in 2008, third in London in 2012, second in Rio in 2016 and fourth in Tokyo in 2020.\", \"from\": 1713, \"to\": 1843, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1751, \"end\": 1758, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999557406062605, \"rank\": 4.426131909893121e-05, \"text\": \"Beijing\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2008_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1777, \"end\": 1783, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999997651757715, \"rank\": 1.5497234275175579e-07, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 1803, \"end\": 1806, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9979944047810437, \"rank\": 0.002009625711660249, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1829, \"end\": 1834, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.8283248849068108, \"rank\": 0.20724435808152278, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the time of writing, Great Britainhas amassed nine gold medals, eight silver and eight bronze, meaning it is now fourth in the Paris 2024 medals table - behind only China, United States and the hosts, France.\", \"from\": 1845, \"to\": 2056, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1985, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.43813985645683e-16, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2013, \"end\": 2018, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9995916672904305, \"rank\": 0.0003812923213247374, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 2020, \"end\": 2033, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9178986353620326, \"rank\": 0.08943986453913483, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 2049, \"end\": 2055, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9647685989636561, \"rank\": 0.02800055279500672, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Few politicians get the legacy they crave.\", \"from\": 2058, \"to\": 2100, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They strive to win a place in history by tackling the big political issues: improving economic growth, transforming the NHS or winning a war.\", \"from\": 2101, \"to\": 2242, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2221, \"end\": 2224, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"score\": 0.9999984455901798, \"rank\": 1.5544043391357888e-06, \"text\": \"NHS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Health_Service\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They rarely succeed in doing any of these things.\", \"from\": 2243, \"to\": 2292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is often the prime ministers considered least successful in political terms whose administrations are remembered for landmark breakthroughs seen as peripheral at the time.\", \"from\": 2294, \"to\": 2468, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"David Cameron, for example,will always be the man who bet the farm on the Brexit referendum\\u2026and lost it all.\", \"from\": 2470, \"to\": 2578, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2470, \"end\": 2483, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Cameron\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.712548728761868e-14, \"text\": \"David Cameron\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Cameron\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Cameron\"}, {\"begin\": 2544, \"end\": 2561, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_United_Kingdom_European_Union_membership_referendum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Brexit referendum\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_United_Kingdom_European_Union_membership_referendum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_United_Kingdom_European_Union_membership_referendum\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But by defying his own party to introduce equal marriage for gays and lesbians - more than half of his parliamentary party refused to vote with him - means he will be seen in a sympathetic light by many for all time.\", \"from\": 2579, \"to\": 2795, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Harold Wilson's Labour governmentsof the 1960s and 70s are synonymous with Britain's economic decline.\", \"from\": 2797, \"to\": 2899, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2797, \"end\": 2810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.170095011666846e-43, \"text\": \"Harold Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harold_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 2813, \"end\": 2819, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"score\": 0.9808707533309701, \"rank\": 0.011671247655067638, \"text\": \"Labour\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_Labour_Party\"}, {\"begin\": 2872, \"end\": 2879, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999957215823663, \"rank\": 3.1172543386767712e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But the abolition of the death penalty and legalisation of abortion in this period changed Britain for ever - and for the better, in the eyes of most.\", \"from\": 2900, \"to\": 3050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2991, \"end\": 2998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999957215823663, \"rank\": 3.1172543386767712e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Tony Blair's reputation is tarnished by the Iraq War.\", \"from\": 3052, \"to\": 3105, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3052, \"end\": 3062, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Blair\", \"score\": 0.9999711966198495, \"rank\": 2.880420995124374e-05, \"text\": \"Tony Blair\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Blair\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Blair\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But in Kosovo, in the Balkans, young adults named\\\"Tonibler\\\"are a testimony to his hero status for stopping the bombing of Kosovo by Serbia in 1999.\", \"from\": 3106, \"to\": 3253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3113, \"end\": 3119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kosovo\", \"score\": 0.9949189824159963, \"rank\": 0.005054332727981045, \"text\": \"Kosovo\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kosovo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kosovo\"}, {\"begin\": 3228, \"end\": 3234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kosovo\", \"score\": 0.9949189824159963, \"rank\": 0.005054332727981045, \"text\": \"Kosovo\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kosovo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kosovo\"}, {\"begin\": 3238, \"end\": 3244, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"score\": 0.928963490002264, \"rank\": 0.07646393763237957, \"text\": \"Serbia\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Serbia\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It seems hard to imagine that either the passage of time, or any as-yet little noticed aspect of the administrations of Boris Johnson or Liz Truss could mitigate their shameful combined record in power.\", \"from\": 3255, \"to\": 3457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3375, \"end\": 3388, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Johnson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.7817185595896744e-23, \"text\": \"Boris Johnson\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Johnson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Boris_Johnson\"}, {\"begin\": 3392, \"end\": 3401, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Liz Truss\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Liz_Truss\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"John Major's name will never appear on the podium of great prime ministers.\", \"from\": 3459, \"to\": 3534, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3459, \"end\": 3469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.620758555161597e-40, \"text\": \"John Major\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/John_Major\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But by creating the National Lottery to build a platform for the never-endingBritish Olympic gold rush- once every four years - this modest man is entitled to take a modest bow.\", \"from\": 3536, \"to\": 3713, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3556, \"end\": 3572, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9790195328852137, \"rank\": 0.021430080186667894, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 3715, \"to\": 3945, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3766, \"end\": 3